   Command	Action
py simulate_attacks.py bruteforce	Simulates a Brute Force login attack (10 failed attempts)
py simulate_attacks.py dos	Simulates a Denial of Service (DoS) flood
py simulate_attacks.py logclear	Simulates an Anti-Forensics event (Security log cleared)
py simulate_attacks.py persistence	Simulates a Malware Persistence attempt (New Service + Task)
py simulate_attacks.py all	Runs all attack simulations sequentially

To check firewall rules:

Step-by-Step Verification:
Check existing rules (to see what's there):
powershell
netsh advfirewall firewall show rule name=all | findstr HybridSIEM
Run the removal command (PowerShell Admin):
powershell
Get-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName "HybridSIEM_Block_*" | Remove-NetFirewallRule
Check again (it should now be empty):
powershell
netsh advfirewall firewall show rule name=all | findstr HybridSIEM